{"type":"message","id":"311d8bf7","parentId":"adfac2dc","timestamp":"2026-02-19T18:09:58.667Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"**Contemplating Implementation Steps**\n\nI've got the text to append and the files identified. Now I'm visualizing the code I'll need. It'll be a loop, iterating through the file list, and within the loop, the logic for appending the text to each file. I'm considering using Python for its file manipulation capabilities, but I still have to see the broader integration.\n\n\n**Initiating the First Action**\n\nAlright, I'm setting up the core of this operation. First, the text string is saved and ready to go. Now, I am pinpointing the first three target files where I'll append the user's specific text. I will start by writing the logic for appending the string to the first specified file.\n\n\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"exec_1771524598543_19","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"Add-Content -Path configs/agents/benjamin_tech.md -Value \"`nCRITICAL PROTOCOL: The task is NEVER considered complete until the Boss has explicitly sent a formatted response to the user via the communication tool.\"\nAdd-Content -Path configs/agents/harper_search.md -Value \"`nCRITICAL PROTOCOL: The task is NEVER considered complete until the Boss has explicitly sent a formatted response to the user via the communication tool.\"\nAdd-Content -Path configs/agents/lucas_qa.md -Value \"`nCRITICAL PROTOCOL: The task is NEVER considered complete until the Boss has explicitly sent a formatted response to the user via the communication tool.\""},"thoughtSignature":""},{"type":"toolCall","id":"exec_1771524598660_20","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"Add-Content -Path SOUL.md -Value \"`nALWAYS_REPLY: At the end of every successful task, you MUST use your output tool to send a summary to Bogdan. Silence is considered a system failure.\""}}],"api":"google-vertex","provider":"google-vertex","model":"gemini-3-pro-preview","usage":{"inpu